Notes on installing the graphical front end for the trust coloring.

This assums a Debian/Ubuntu system.

1) Install Mysql
sudo apt-get install mysql-server mysql-client
 
2) Install apache, php
sudo apt-get install apache2 php5 php5-mysql php-config libapache2-mod-python

2.1) Configure apache

cd /etc/apache2/
Create the file sites-availible/wiki-site

NameVirtualHost *:10301
<VirtualHost *:10301>
	ServerAdmin webmaster@localhost
	
	DocumentRoot /var/www/wikis/1
	<Directory />
		Options FollowSymLinks
		AllowOverride None
	</Directory>
	<Directory /var/www/wikis/1>
		Options Indexes FollowSymLinks MultiViews
		AllowOverride None
		Order allow,deny
		allow from all
	</Directory>

	ErrorLog /var/log/apache2/error.log

	# Possible values include: debug, info, notice, warn, error, crit,
	# alert, emerg.
	LogLevel warn

	CustomLog /var/log/apache2/access.log combined
	ServerSignature On

</VirtualHost>

cd sites-enabled
rm *
ln -s ../sites-availible/wiki-site

edit ports.conf to look like:

#Listen 80
Listen 10301

<IfModule mod_ssl.c>
       Listen 443
</IfModule>

Restart Apache
sudo /etc/init.d/apache2 restart

3) Install mediawiki

Go here: http://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Download
And download the latest version of MediaWiki

untar it (tar -zxf mediawiki.tar.gz)

and copy it to the directory /var/www/wikis/1

mv ./mediawiki /var/www/wikis/1

Now, go here:
http://128.114.63.182:10301 (Replacing 128.114.63.182 with your
system's IP)

(Note -- this may require bridged networking for VMWare to work -- I'm
not sure.)

Follow the directions to install. Do NOT choose any caching types --
caching is not needed for tests and makes debugging the php very hard.

4) Install trust coloring extensions 

cd /var/www/wikis/1/extensions
ln -s git/wikitrust/batch/mediawiki/extensions/Trust .

cd ../skins
ln -s /home/ipye/git/wikitrust/batch/mediawiki/skins/* .

Edit these values in LocalSettings.php
$wgDefaultSkin = 'trust';

And add this at the bottom:
require_once( $IP . "/extensions/Trust/Trust3.php" );

Other extensions can be also added to make the text look good. 
Currently, we are using these extensions on the live demo:

AntiSpoof     DeletedContributions	  LinkSearch	Oversight	 SpamBlacklist
AssertEdit    ExpandTemplates		  LuceneSearch	ParserFunctions  SyntaxHighlight_GeSHi
CategoryTree  ExtMan.php		  Makesysop	Poem		 Trust
CharInsert    Filepath			  Newuserlog	ProofreadPage	 UsernameBlacklist
CheckUser     Gadgets			  Nuke		Quiz		 wikihiero
Cite	      ImageMap			  OAI		README
ConfirmEdit   LabeledSectionTransclusion  OggHandler	Renameuser

This is all you need to do. The next time you load a page in the wiki,
if there is trust-colored information, it will be displayed.